The paper discusses visualisation techniques for multi-objective optimisation, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on evolutionary multi-objective optimisation algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the exploration of trade-off relationships, which is a topic that falls under the category of decision support systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of multivariate data, which is a topic that falls under the categories of data science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
